The Vita FPGA Architecture Synthesizer Subproject is a program designed
to synthesize the source code written in the Verilog-2005 programming
language into a bitstream that the Vita FPGA Architecture can run.

The Vita FPGA Architecture Synthesizer Subproject is under development,
and is licensed under The VitaSet License.

The bitstreams produced can be run on computer chips that have the
Vita FPGA Architecture in them, or by using the Vita FPGA Architecture
Emulator Subproject with enough memory and patience. However, you can
still quit the Vita FPGA Architecture Emulator Subproject program at
any time with Ctrl + C, but all of your progress may be lost. You can
also quit the Vita FPGA Architecture Synthesizer Subproject program at
any time with Ctrl + C, but all of your progress may be lost.

Future backends to the Vita FPGA Architecture Emulator can reduce the
amount of patience required with their increased performance.

The Vita FPGA Architecture Emulator Subproject currently supports using
a single x86_64 CPU core as its backend. However, if you would like to
contribute new backends, then you are welcome to do so, so long as you
agree that your contributions to the Vita FPGA Architecture Emulator
Subproject will be licensed under The VitaSet license.

A backend that would be welcome to see, would be a GPGPU backend.
